caption.center: State of Utah, Plaintiff and Appellee, v. Miguel J. Gutierrez-Torrez,

posture.unpublished: [EDITOR'S NOTE: This case is unpublished as indicated by the issuing court.] Appeal from the First District, Logan Department, The Honorable Gordon J. Low.

attorneys.unpublished:
Todd A. Utzinger, Bountiful, for Appellant.
Mark L. Shurtleff and Laura B. Dupaix, Salt Lake City, for Appellee.

panel.unpublished: Before Judges Bench, Davis, and Jackson.

opinion_text.unpublished:
This case is before the court on Plaintiff's motion to dismiss for lack of jurisdiction on the basis that Defendant failed to make a timely motion to the trial court to withdraw his guilty plea. See State v. Reyes, 2002 UT 13, ¶¶ 3-4, 40 P.3d 630. Defendant concedes that this court lacks jurisdiction over this appeal.
Accordingly, Defendant's appeal is dismissed.
Russell W. Bench, Associate Presiding Judge, James Z. Davis, Judge, Norman H. Jackson, Judge.
